---
description: Premium UI and UX quality rules for the Aureline renderer
globs:
  - "app/renderer/**"
  - "packages/ui/**"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Aureline must feel like a premium product, not a starter template; use owned design tokens and consistent typography and spacing.
- Implement truthful empty, loading, error, and success states; never fake engine state.
- Support keyboard navigation, visible focus, accessible labels, and light/dark/system themes.
- Handle desktop resizing without clipped critical controls or broken hierarchy.
- Prefer progressive disclosure and an image-first creative workflow.
- Do not use emoji as product icons or scatter inline styles.
- Give every component clear ownership and a focused public surface.
- Review visual changes in the running UI across themes and representative sizes.
